This paper involves the optimization of FPGA placement using evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and digital circuits (cs.DC). The use of systolic arrays and pipelining also relates to embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of SLR replication and placement and routing flow suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
